So `toFun (Fin.last n) (lens.proj outerStmtIn) transcript` is `stF (Fin.last n) (lens.proj outerStmtIn) transcript`.

Thus, `hStmt` is `¬(stF (Fin.last n) (lens.proj outerStmtIn) transcript)`.

Now, the `toFun_empty` is `fun outerStmtIn => sorry`. This is empty, so it doesn't contribute to the probability.

The `toFun_next` is `fun m hDir outerStmtIn transcript hStmt msg => sorry`. This is also empty.

The `toFun_full` is `fun outerStmtIn transcript hStmt => sorry`.

So, all the components of the state function are empty except for `toFun`.

Therefore, the probability `Pr[fun x => x ∈ outerLangOut | run_simulate init impl (Verifier.liftContext ...)]` is `0`.

